column7: The VSP crew attended the grand opening of Quiver Surf Shop and Shaper Studios in Maitencillo last week! It was great to connect with more people within the surf community and understand the process of how surfboards are shaped. We hope to collaborate with Quiver in the future! // El equipo VSP asistió la inauguración de la tienda de surf Quiver y Shaper Studios en Maitencillo la semana pasada! Fue un placer conectar con gente dentro de la comunidad de surf y entender el proceso de cómo se fabrica las tablas de surf. ¡Esperamos colaborar con Quiver en el futuro!  #valposurf #quiver #shaperstudios #community #comunidad

column7:
The ocean is very fun, but Mother Nature is also very strong. We found this helpful diagram to make sure that time in the waves is safe and enjoyable. //
El mar es muy divertido, pero también la Madre Naturaleza es muy fuerte. Encontramos esta gráfica muy útil para asegurarse de que su paseo en la playa sea seguro y agradable. #surf #chile #valposurf #mothernature

Summer surf sessions begin with a splash! 
During the summer holidays in Valparaíso, VSP is offering summer surf sessions for each neighborhood twice a week. Five days full of surfing fun! //
¡Las sesiones de surf ya comenzaron!
Durante las vacaciones de verano en Valparaíso, VSP está ofreciendo sesiones de surf para cada grupo dos veces a la semana. ¡Cinco días llenos de diversión y surf! 
#vsp #youthmentorship #surf #chile #valposurf #verano #summer

column7:
Uno de los premios a la sostenibilidad más importantes del mundo, Energy Globe World Awards, entregó sus galardones el recién pasado 19 de Enero
Nuestro país también participó con el proyecto Valpo Surf Project.
También hubo premiación especial a Construcción Sustentable: Construcción Verde y Mejores prácticas de sustentabilidad: proyecto “Mega Pars” Irán, que manifiesta un alto grado de sustentabilidad en todas las áreas evaluadas.

Los ganadores y premiados fueron
-	Global y Categoría Tierra: Proyectos de reforestación de la Fundación Suiza Etiopía Verde, Etiopía
-	Categoría Fuego: Cómo el agua y blanqueador hacen un Litro de luz. Filipinas
-	Categoría Agua: Filtros de tiestos de cerámica para tratamiento del agua. República Unida de Tanzania
-	Categoría Aire: Camión con alimentación eléctrica para el transporte de bienes. Suiza
-	Categoría Joven: Copa Agua fresca - Torneo de futbol medioambiental. Belice
-	Premio Especial: Construcción Verde y Mejores prácticas de sustentabilidad: proyecto “Mega Pars” Irán, que manifiesta un alto grado de sustentabilidad en todas las áreas evaluadas.


http://www.energyglobe.info/en/world-awards/winnerandfinalists/

column7: We recently had the opportunity partner with Fútbol Más, a nonprofit organization that uses soccer to instill respect, responsibility, and leadership in the disadvantaged youth they serve. Read more about this our latest blog post. // Recientemente tuvimos la oportunidad de realizar actividades junto al equipo de Fútbol +, ésta es una organización que utiliza el fútbol para desarrollar valores como el respeto, la responsabilidad y el liderazgo junto a los niños, niñas y jóvenes con los que trabajan. Lea más acerca de esto en nuestra última publicación en nuestro blog. http://ow.ly/V2AAe

column7: We're not just about surfing here at VSP! We encourage our students to participate in skateboarding and soccer, along with any other sport that can teach the the reward in practicing to improve! // aquí en VSP no sólo surfeamos! Animamos a nuestros estudiantes a patinar y jugar fútbol, y cualquier otro deporte que les enseña sobre la recompensa de la práctica! #VSP #valposurfproject #skateon #youthmentorship

column7: With the holiday season approaching, many of us will be shopping for gifts online. You can give even more while using Amazon via their giving program, Amazon Smile. When you are logged into Amazon Smile, Amazon donates .5% of your purchases to the charity of your choice at no extra cost to you. In this week’s blog post, read about how you can support VSP // La navidad se acerca y muchos de nosotros estaremos comprando en línea. Puedes dar mucho más mientras utilizas Amazon, a través de su programa Amazon Smile. Mientras ingresas en Amazon Smile, Amazon donará .5% de tu compra a una organización benéfica de tu elección sin costo extra para ti. Lea en la publicación de esta semana del blog los detalles de cómo puede ayudar a VSP este año. http://ow.ly/UCBG6

column7: Yesterday with the advanced group in Cerro Mariposa, we played Jeopardy, with categories including Calvin & Hobbes, in which you had to explain the joke of a Calvin & Hobbes comic strip; Surf; Teacher Trivia; Translations; Tongue Twisters; and Question Words. Defying the confines of their name, Team "i don't know" took an early lead, but in the end Team "eh." caught up and the game ended in a tie, 5100-5100.   //   Ayer con el grupo avanzado de Cerro Mariposas jugamos Jeopardy, con las siguientes categorias: Calvin & Hobbes, en la que había que explicar la broma en un cómic de Calvin & Hobbes; Surf; Datos Curiosos de las Tías; Traducciones, Trabalenguas, y Palabras de Preguntas. Resistiendo los limites de su nombre, el equipo "i don't know" tomó una temprana delantera, pero al final, el equipo "eh." remontó y el partido terminó empatado 5100-5100.

column7:
The Valpo Surf Project has weekly programming that not only has the intent of forming mentoring relationships with its students, but also is designed to help them reap the benefits of speaking two languages. This week we discovered ways to be further assured that it’s worth it to speak another language. // Cada semana, Valpo Surf Project realiza actividades que no sólo tienen la intención de generar vínculos con sus estudiantes, sino también están diseñadas para ayudarles a cosechar las ventajas de hablar dos idiomas. Esta semana en el blog, reafirmamos que vale la pena hablar otro idioma.
http://valposurfproject.com/the-benefits-of-learning-english-as-a-second-language/

column7:
Recently, the Valpo Surf Project (VSP) was invited to send some of its students to participate in the Our Ocean Science Camp (put on by Fundación Ciencia Joven) in Valparaíso. This camp was organized as a part of the Our Ocean Conference, and was designed to teach students who attend public schools and are in either the 5th or 6th grade about the conservation of the species and ecosystems that inhabit the sea. Read about their experience in our latest blog post! // Recientemente, Valpo Surf Project (VSP) fue invitado a participar del Campamento Científico Nuestro Océano en Valparaíso. Esta actividad, organizada en el marco de la conferencia Nuestro Océano, estuvo diseñada para educar a estudiantes de 5to y 6to básico, pertenecientes a escuelas públicas, sobre la conservación de las especies y ecosistemas que habitan en el mar. Lea sobre su experiencia en la última publicación del blog!
http://valposurfproject.com/our-ocean-science-camp/

column7: This is Maximiliano preparing to catch a wave with previous VSP student turned instructor, Claudio. As a student of the Valpo Surf Project, Maxi has a place that he can focus on his personal development. Every time he stands up on the board he rides each wave with a smile that stretches ear to ear. // Maximiliano se prepara agarrar una ola con nuestro instructor de surf, Claudio. Como un estudiante de Valpo Surf Project, Maxi tiene un lugar donde puede enfocar en desarrollo personal. Cada vez que agarra una ola tiene una sonrisa grande en su cara. #surf #vsp

column7:
At the Valpo Surf Project we are very fortunate to have supporters who come from various backgrounds and are based in different parts of the world. As recipients of the SIMA Humanitarian Fund, Stokes Me is one of these influential supporters. Read this week’s blog to learn more about their September campaign. // Aquí en Valpo Surf Project somos muy afortunados de tener distintas fuentes de apoyo provenientes de diversos contextos y ubicaciones del mundo. Como beneficiarios del fond humanitario SIMA, StokesMe es uno de estos donantes influyentes. Lea la publicación del blog para aprender más sobre su campaña en septiembre!
http://valposurfproject.com/support-from-stokesmes-september-campaign/

On 16 September 2015, an 8.3 magnitude earthquake struck the coast of central Chile, triggering tsunami waves in certain cities. Although we are happy to report the safety of our team and students, the beach where we surf has suffered significant damage. Read more about the disaster in this week's blog. // El 16 de septiembre de 2015, un terremoto de magnitud 8.3 (Richter) golpeó a la costa central de Chile, provocando alertas de tsunami y evacuaciones costeras. Aunque nuestro equipo, estudiantes y voluntarios se encuentran todos bien, nos encontramos muy afectados por el daño causado por olas del tsunami a la playa donde surfeamos cada semana. Lee más sobre el desastre en la nueva publicación del blog.
http://valposurfproject.com/after-the-tsunami-damage-to-local-beaches/

column7: Did you know: A recent study shows that 88% of the millennial generation prefer collaboration and teamwork over competition because they feel more valuable? Just another reason we like to work as a team! // ¿Sabías que: Un estudio reciente muestra que el 88% de la generación milenaria prefiere la colaboración y el trabajo en equipo sobre la competencia, debido a que se sienten más valiosos? ¡Otra razón por la que nos gusta el trabajo en equipo! #vsp #valposurfproject #factoftheday #teamwork

column7:
The Valpo Surf Project is celebrating Chile's Independence Day! We are very excited that we can be a part of this beautiful celebration and pay respect to the great country and its people with whom we work. ¡Viva Chile! // Valpo Surf Project está celebrando las Fiestas Patrias de Chile! Estamos muy emocionados de poder ser parte de esta celebración hermosa y ofrecer respeto al gran país y a su gente con quienes trabajamos. ¡Viva Chile!
http://valposurfproject.com/celebrating-chiles-independence-day/

column7: Have you practiced your pop-up lately? Every surf session before we get in the water the VSP collectively practices our surfing form - just one of the reasons we have so many awesome surfers! // ¿Has practicado tu “pop-up” recientemente? En cada sesión de surf, antes de entrar en el mar, practicamos en conjunto nuestro estilo - sólo una de las razones que tenemos muchos surfistas! #vsp #valposurf #surf

The VSP recently challenged their students to bring recyclable materials from home with the desire that they would create something entirely new and useful. Check out their creations on this week's blog! // VSP desafió a sus estudiantes que trajeran materiales reciclables desde sus casas, con la intención que crear algo completamente nuevo y útil. ¡Lee la publicación nueva del blog para ver sus creaciones! #vsp #valposurfproject #reduce #reuse #recycle

column7:
Be a part of the Stokes Me fundraising initiative put on by the SIMA Humanitarian Fund! The Valpo Surf Project is 1 of the 15 StokesME beneficiaries who are focusing on improving the quality of life, health, and welfare of people around the world // Se parte de la iniciativa para recaudar fondos de StokesMe por el fondo humanitario SIMA! Valpo Surf Project es 1 de los 15 beneficiarios de StokesME que se enfocan en la mejora de la calidad de vida, salud y bienestar de personas de todo el mundo #valposurf

column7:
At the Valpo Surf Project we see ourselves as more than just English teachers & surf instructors. Check out this week's blog for a deeper look at the role of our "tíos" // En Valpo Surf Project nos vemos a nosotros mismos como algo más que profesores de inglés o instructores de surf. column7: Today the Valpo Surf Project celebrates the International Youth Day! This year’s focus is civic engagement and we are so proud of how the communities that we work with come together to be a collective source of change! // Hoy Valpo Surf Project está celebrando el Día Internacional de Juventud! column7:
What can we do with all of that trash we picked up at the beach recently? See how this board shaper is creating surfboards from reclaimed litter. “I was inspired by the a mix of a love for the ocean and feeling so agonized by the amount of trash washing up on the beaches, that I felt compelled to try to do something to combat the problem.” // ¿Qué podemos hacer con toda esa basura que recogimos de la playa recientemente? Mira cómo este hombre crea tablas de surf de la basura recogida. “Mi inspiración viene de una mezcla entre el amor por el océano y un sentimiento tormentoso por la cantidad de basura que encuentras en las playas, por lo que me sentí obligado a tratar de hacer algo para combatir el problema”.

http://ilivextreme.com/surfboards-made-from-marine-debris/

column7: SURF INTERNSHIP WITH GREAT CAUSE - The Valpo Surf Project  internship. This is working for an NGO located in Valparaíso, Chile. This NGO uses the tools of surfing, English, and environmental awareness to engage, empower, and teach values like perseverance, leadership, and responsibility to at-risk youth from Valparaíso. Great cause! http://www.idealist.org/view/internship/NZBFtMf24w4/

column7: Last day to get your tickets to the VSP Boston Silent Auction Fundraiser! Online presale tickets are only $35 but running out. Get yours now at: https://vsp2015boston.eventbrite.com. Drinks served by Samuel Adams, KEEL, Downeast Cider House, and Gosling's Rum. Food from Flatbread Somerville and Anna's Taqueria! Phenomenal silent auction items including memorabilia, jewelry, and professional photography from Chris Burkard Photography. Looking forward to seeing everyone there!

column7: New England friends of VSP, tickets are going fast to our Annual Boston Silent Auction Fundraiser! This Saturday, May 30th we invite you to the Impact Hub Boston to share an evening of great food, drinks, and company to support our program in Chile. Awesome auction items this year including prints from Ryan Struck Photography, Chris Burkard Photography, items from Artemis Design Co., and more! Food and beverages by Samuel Adams, Gosling's Rum, KEEL, Downeast Cider House, Flatbread Somerville, and Anna's Taqueria. Buy your tickets before they run out! Share the event through the facebook page and spread the word! http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-boston-2015-silent-auction-fundraiser-tickets-16412871340

column7: Even with winter on it's way here in Chile, falling temps won't scare the VSP from getting to the beach! No matter what hemisphere you're in, we hope everyone can get out there and catch some waves this weekend! // Aún cuando el invierno está muy cerca acá en Chile, las bajas temperaturas no alejan al VSP de la playa! Sin importar el hemisferio en que te encuentres ubicado, esperamos que tod@s puedan ir a la playa y agarrar olas este fin de semana! #vsp #surf #felizviernes #surfsomething #chile

column7: Les invitamos este sábado 9 de Mayo desde las 10:00 a las 16:00 hrs. a la Feria Social y Deportiva de Playa Ancha. La actividad se realizará en la cancha El Hoyo de Montedónico. Se desarrollarán muchas actividades en las cuales estaremos ofreciendo talleres de surf y patineta! Para más información vean el link, los esperamos! // We invite you to the Feria Social y Deportiva de Playa Ancha this Saturday, May 9th, from 10:00 am to 4:00 pm in the court El Hoyo de Montedónico. Join us for surf and skateboarding workshops! Check out the link for more information, see you then!

column7:
In honor of Earth Day, we would like to spread the word about a cause that means a lot to the Valpo Surf Project. Check out our blog to read about the effort to preserve Punta de Lobos, a world-renowned Chilean point break under threat of development.  Save The Waves Patagonia Chile Ramon Navarro #LobosPorSiempre
http://valposurfproject.com/?p=2847&preview=true

column7: A new study from Science Magazine shows that the amount of plastic dumped into the ocean each year equals five grocery bags per every foot of coastline. Use less plastic and help keep the coast clean for all to enjoy! // Un nuevo estudio de Science Magazine demuestra que la cantidad de plástico botada en el océano cada año, es igual que cinco bolsas de plástico por cada pie de costa. ¡Usa menos plástico y ayuda a mantener la costa limpia para que todos la puedan disfrutar! #medioambiente #environment #educate @Natgeo

column7:
Support the VSP Before the End of the Year at http://valposurfproject.com/donate-now/.

Your tax deductible gift will make a big difference for our students in 2015.  

We empower our students with the tools to better their own lives and positively impact their communities.  Your support is essential to help us shape leaders like Claudio, our first student who returned as a mentor to influence the VSP's next generation. Watch the video at https://vimeo.com/97902706 to hear his story and learn about the powerful impact your donation will have in our students’ lives.

column7:
Last week VSP participated in the FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf in Santiago. Congratulations to all the organizations and films that were involved in this awesome event, Puertecillo Playas Libres, Punta de Lobos por Siempre, GiveSurf, Patagonia Chile, Sanuk Chile, Cerveza Corona Chile, Farias Moreno Photography.
Check out our latest blog post to read and see photos from the event. 
http://valposurfproject.com/ficsurf-international-surf-film-festival/

column7:
No se olviden a reservar las fechas 25-28 de noviembre para asistir al FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf en Centro Cultural Las Condes.  100% del dinero recaudado por las entradas beneficia a las ONGs invitadas.  Eligen a The Valpo Surf Project cuando compran sus entradas para destinar su aporte!  

Save the dates November 25-28 to attend FICSURF CHILE - Chile's International Surf Film Festival at Centro Cultural Las Condes.  100% of ticket sales benefit the NGOs partnered with the festival.  Choose Valpo Surf Project when buying tickets to support the organization!

column7:
Last Friday October 17, 2014, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its Sixth Annual NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser in Manhattan with more than 175 people in attendance, the event was VSP’s best attended and most successful fundraiser to date.  We would like to especially thank everyone who attended and our event sponsors including the Centre for Social Innovation NYC, Runa Clean Energy Drinks, Frava Naturally Caffeinated Juice, and Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. for contributing to such a successful event.

We’d also like to extend our thanks to all of the donors who contributed to the success of the silent auction, including surf photographers Ryan Struck, Chris Burkard, Donald Crisitellio, Ryan Mack, and  Andreea Waters; custom surfboards from Malwitz Custom Surfboards and Union Surfboards; surf gear and gift certificates from Patagonia Surf Bowery, Barewires Surf Shop, Jake’s Surf Shop, Lost Weekend NYC Surf, Saturdays Surf NYC, Evil Paradise, Rareform, Spellbinders Surf and Snow, Summer Love Surfing and Yoga and  Pigdog Surf Academy (Springlake); artists Brainstorm Print and Design, Billy Name, Jeff Armstrong, Lexie Smith, Artemis Design Co., Sarah Oliver Handbags, Ali Cherkis, Ann Marie Steuber,  Lizzie Meltzer, Virgina Lunt; and local businesses Chelsea Williams Sonoma, Feel Food, DASH, Beach Haus Beer Co., Brooklyn Boulders, Bucketfeet, Carton Brewing Co., Manhattan Plaza Health Club, Ovest Pizzoteca, Rad Cakes Apparel,Shake Shack, Spitzer’s Corner, The Eddie’s Pizza Truck, Totto, The Eddie’s Pizza Truck, Georgette Keenan of Necessities for the Heart, Chronicle Books, Scholastic Books,  Yogamaya, and YogaWorks.  

This event could not have been possible without the support of the entire VSP staff, and our NYC event organizing committee including event coordinator Sam Rigby, VSP Global board of directors member Ryan Holbrook, and event committee members Nick Napolitano, Jenna Barzelay, Manuela Odell, Jennifer McInnis, James Lunt, Patrick Flaherty, Dean Thompson, Mark Thompson, Basil Henning, and Sara Hames; and our amazing volunteer staff including bar tender extraordinaires Michael Hansen and Alexandre Bacon and event photographer Caitlyn Warakomski.  

_______________________________

  
El viernes pasado 17 de octubre 2014, Valpo Surf Project se llevó a cabo su Sexto Evento Anual de Recaudar Fondos en NYC en Manhattan; asistido por mas que 175 personas, fue el evento más exitoso de la historia de VSP.  Queremos agradecer todas las personas que asistieron y los auspiciadores del evento incluyendo Centre for Social Innovation NYC, Runa Clean Energy Drinks, Frava Naturally Caffeinated Juice, y Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. por contribuir a un evento tan exitoso.

También nos gustaría agradecer todos los donantes que contribuyeron al remate incluyendo fotógrafos de surf Ryan Struck, Chris Burkard, Donald Crisitellio, Ryan Mack, y  Andreea Waters; tablas de surf a medida por Malwitz Custom Surfboards y Union Surfboards; equipo de surf y certificados de Patagonia Surf Bowery, Barewires Surf Shop, Jake’s Surf Shop, Lost Weekend NYC Surf, Saturdays Surf NYC, Evil Paradise, Rareform, Spellbinders Surf and Snow, Summer Love Surfing and Yoga and  Pigdog Surf Academy (Springlake); artistas Brainstorm Print and Design, Billy Name, Jeff Armstrong, Lexie Smith, Artemis Design Co., Sarah Oliver Handbags, Ali Cherkis, Ann Marie Steuber,  Lizzie Meltzer, Virgina Lunt; y negocios locales Chelsea Williams Sonoma, Feel Food, DASH, Beach Haus Beer Co., Brooklyn Boulders, Bucketfeet, Carton Brewing Co., Manhattan Plaza Health Club, Ovest Pizzoteca, Rad Cakes Apparel,Shake Shack, Spitzer’s Corner, The Eddie’s Pizza Truck, Totto, The Eddie’s Pizza Truck, Georgette Keenan de Necessities for the Heart, Chronicle Books, Scholastic Books,  Yogamaya, y YogaWorks.  

This event could not have been possible without the support of the entire VSP staff, and our NYC event organizing committee including event coordinator Este evento no habría sido posible sin el apoyo del staff administrativo del VSP, y el comité del evento de NYC incluyendo el coordinador del evento Sam Rigby, miembro del directorio de VSP Global y miembros del comité del evento Nick Napolitano, Jenna Barzelay, Manuela Odell, Jennifer McInnis, James Lunt, Patrick Flaherty, Dean Thompson, Mark Thompson, Basil Henning, y Sara Hames; y nuestro equipo de voluntarios incluyendo los bartenders Michael Hansen y Alexandre Bacon y fotógrafa Caitlyn Warakomski.

column7:
Come join the VSP team tomorrow, Friday October 17, from 7-11 PM at Centre for Social Innovation for our @Valpo Surf Project's NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser sponsored by Runa, Frava, & Sierra Nevada Brewing Company. Purchase advanced tickets for $35 at http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-projects-nyc-silent-auction-fundraiser-tickets-12939306815

Check out some silent auction items from Malwitz Custom Surfboards, Union Surfboards, Patagonia Surf Bowery Chris Burkard Photography, Ryan Struck Photography!

column7: Only FOUR more DAYS to enter the BBSF Surf Shorts Film Comp presented by GoPro! The theme is ‘Citizens of the Sea’ and the time limit TEN minutes. Get yours in THIS WEEKEND! Enter at http://surfshorts.byronbaysurffestival.com/ Also, just by voting you could win a prize—support your friends and local filmmakers and check it out!

Estamos bien emocionados por haber sido seleccionados como semifinalista en el concurso 2014 de AccionJovenChile, organizado en conjunción con Universidad Andrés Bello y The International Youth Foundation. JAC Chile Derco DercoCenter 

We're very excited to have been selected as semi-finalists for the 2014 Acción Joven Chile grant, organized in conjunction with Universidad Andrés Bello and the International Youth Foundation.

column7:
At the VSP blog, you can catch up on Nat, one of this year's interns. Now back in the United States to continue her university studies, this spotlight is on Natalie Valentin who came to Valparaíso with an adventurous spirit, and hard-working, passionate attitude. Click below to see some wonderful photos & see everything she has contributed to The Valpo Surf Project.
~~~~~~
En el blog de VSP, puedes cachar que tal con Natalie, uno de los practicantes del año. Ahora en los EEUU a seguir estudiando en la U, este foco de atención es de Natalie Valentin, que vino a Valparaíso con un espíritu aventurera y pasión para el proyecto. Mira abajo a ver más fotos y leer todo que hizo en su tiempo con VSP. 

http://valposurfproject.com/intern-spotlight-natalie-valentin/

column7:
Thanks again to everyone who came out to support the VSP's 2014 San Francisco Silent Auction Fundraiser at Impact Hub Bay Area in mid-July including more than 75 attendees and our food and beverage sponsors Sailor Jerry, Magnolia Gastropub & Brewery, Sabores del Sur, The Little Chihuahua Mexican Restaurant, and Whole Foods Market, Franklin.

Huge thanks to all of the artists and local businesses who donated to the silent auction including Brainstorm, Chris Burkard Photography, 21st Amendment Brewery, Proof Lab, Bourbon and Branch, Chronicle Books, Tacolicious, Patagonia San Francisco, RareForm, Yoga Tree, Planet Granite - Climbing Yoga Fitness, Mission Cliffs Indoor Rock Climbing Gym, Park District Coffee Co., San Francisco CrossFit, Bi-Rite Market, Man Crates, Homewood Mountain Resort, and Lemonwood Imprints!

Photo credit: Allison Marshall.

column7:
¡Feliz cumple Claudio! A very happy birthday to our friend Claudio, the first ever Valpo Surf Project student who has come back as a junior tío. The team is so proud of you, enjoy your day! #valposurf #youthmentorship
~~~~~~~~~~
¡Feliz cumple Claudio! Deseamos un cumpleaños muy feliz a nuestro amigo Claudio, el primer alumno del VSP que ha vuelto a enseñar como un tío. El equipo es orgulloso de ti, que disfrutes de tu día!

column7:
A few weekends ago, The Valpo Surf Project took their students from Laguna Verde, Cerro Mariposa and Cerro Toro took the local rock-climb gym Tornamesa Centro de Escalada for a fun day of adventure. To read more about our excursion and see what else we've been up to this winter, check out our blog.
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Unos fin de semanas pasados, el VSP y sus alumnos de Laguna Verde, Cerro Mariposa, y Cerro Toro fueron al gimnasio local Tornamesa por un día de aventura. A leer más sobre la excursíon y ver que hacemos este invierno, mira a nuestra blog.

http://valposurfproject.com/tornamesa-field-trip/

column7:
Join the VSP tonight at Impact Hub Bay Area for our Silent Auction Fundraiser. Get your ticket before 5pm here: http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-2014-san-francisco-silent-auction-event-tickets-12037585743

Impact Hub Bay Area is located at 901 Mission St. San Francisco, CA. Support a great cause during an evening full of food, drinks, and bidding on a variety of great silent auction items from local artists and businesses. 

Tickets are $25 in advance or $35 at the door.

Be sure to bring card or cash for silent auction purchases!

No need to bring paper copy of ticket, once tickets are purchased, your name will be placed on a guest list at the door. Hope to see you there!

column7:
Come join members of the The Valpo Surf Project team on Friday, July 11 from 7-10 PM at Impact Hub Bay Area located at 901 Mission St. San Francisco, CA, for an evening of food, drinks, and bidding on a variety of great silent auction items from local artists and businesses. 

The event consists of an open bar courtesy of Sailor Jerry Rum and Magnolia Gastropub & Brewery, as well as hors d'oeuvres provided by The Little Chihuahua Mexican Restaurant and Sabores del Sur

Silent Auction items donated from Anderson Surfboards, Proof Lab Surf Shop, Brainstorm Print and Design, 21st Amendment Brewery, Chris Burkard Photography, Chronicle Books, Tacolicious, RareForm, Yoga Tree, Mission Cliffs Indoor Rock Climbing Gym, Planet Granite San Francisco, Taylor Stitch, Park District Coffee Co., Patagonia San Francisco, Whole Foods Market, Franklin and many more. 
        
Tickets are $25 in advance or $35 at the door.
Purchase here: http://www.eventbrite.com/e/valpo-surf-project-2014-san-francisco-silent-auction-event-tickets-12037585743

Be sure to bring card or cash for silent auction purchases!

No need to bring paper copy of ticket, once tickets are purchased, your name will be placed on a guest list at the door. Hope to see you there!

column7:
Read our newest blog post about the adventure to the sand dunes in ConCon. Our students spent the day learning to sand board, playing frisbee, and getting a lesson on the environment & history of this local landmark.
~~~~

http://valposurfproject.com/day-at-the-dunes/

column7:
This #weekend, VSP students got to try for the first time climbing & bouldering at Tornamesa Centro de Escalada the #local rock #gym. With boundless energy, our students were up and down the walls like naturals.
~~~~~~
Este fin de semana, los alumnos del VSP fueron para la primera vez al Tornamesa Centro de Escalada, el gimnasio local de escalar, a tratar un deporte nuevo. Con tanta energía, los chicos estuvieron como escaladores naturales! 

Muchas gracias a Tornamesa por todo la ayuda y el espacio de taller.

column7:
During last week's activity at El Centro Cultural El Trafon, VSP students made #art projects out of #recyclable materials. Here, Noelia & Claudio are painting their plastic bottle bird-feeders. #valposurf #youthmentorship #environment #educate
~~~
El domingo pasado en el centro cultural El Trafon, los alumnos del VSP hicieron proyectos del arte con materias de reciclaje. Aquí, Noelia y Claudio pintan sus comedores de pájaros hecho por botellas de plastica. 

Trafon albergue autogestionado #FuerzaValpo

column7:
NGO Surf Program Looking for Intern Applicants! Deadline approaching! 

Interested in the surf? Working with kids? Taking care of our environment? Want to step outside your comfort zone & make a true difference? The Valpo Surf Project is looking for several-self motivated interns to join the team in Valparaíso, Chile for 12 months, working to educate and mentor the youth of the city.

Fill out an application before the June 30th deadline. Read here for full details and information.
http://www.idealist.org/view/internship/kpHfN7h4TbfP/

column7:
Since the wildfires happened in Valparaiso in April, the VSP has been diligently working to reconstruct a home in Cerro Litre with a team of two architects and many volunteers. Check out the newest blog post for updates on the Olson Family House and the impressive progress the Valpo Surf Project has made.
~~~~~~~~~
Desde abril, cuando pasaron los incendios en Valparaíso, el VSP ha estado trabajando diligentemente para reconstruir una casa en Cerro Litre con un equipo de dos arquitectos y muchos voluntarios. Mira el nuevo post de blog para más información sobre La Casa de Familia Olson y el impresionante progreso que ha hecho el Valpo Surf Project.

http://valposurfproject.com/fuerza-valparaiso-update-on-the-olson-family-house/

column7:
On May 31, 2014 Valpo Surf Project hosted its most successful and best attended fundraiser to date at Impact Hub Boston with sponsorship from Downeast Cider House, Gosling's Rum, Sierra Nevada, Flatbread Somerville and Anna's Taqueria.

With more than 165 people in attendance, the event was a great opportunity to raise funds and awareness for the Valpo Surf Project’s programming, and to premier a recent documentary about Claudio, our first student with the Valpo Surf Project who has recently become a junior surf instructor and mentor with the VSP.

A huge contribution to the event’s success was through donations of silent auction items from local businesses such as Chino Surf boards, Brooklyn Boulders Somerville, The Institute of Contemporary Art/Boston, Cuppow, Jiberish, Vans, Taza Chocolate, Cambridge Naturals, Porter Square Books, b.good, Boston Sports Club, ACK Surf School, Tenoch Mexican, Camp Waziyatah, Pretty Things Beer & Ale Project, Mary Tiseo, George Pillsbury, and Pepita Soto. The silent auction also showcased work from Pescadotes, Brainstorm, Chris Burkard Photography, Clarkography, Ryan Struck Photography, and local artists Albie Davis, Pat Falco, Erik Heumiller, Jeff Armstrong, and Coastal Creations by the Maine Milk Maiden.

Thank you so much to everyone who made this event such a success, including Impact Hub Boston, all of our food and beverage sponsors, silent auction donors, all of the guests who attended, production company Herman Mantis for photo and video assistance.

The VSP team would like to specifically thank all of the volunteers who contributed to the planning and execution of the event, particularly our event coordinator Amanda Pillsbury and our volunteer team including Kait Barlow, Nina Berg, Kate Brown, Brendan Buckland, Peter Griffith, Ned Rich, Paula Hernandez, Tallulah Knopp, Lily Kofke, Tom Meehan, Seth Myer, Nick Napolitano, Josie Reinhardt, Helen Sullivan, Pennie Taylor, Kristofer Tupper, and Amanda Vernon.  

Much thanks to our incredible intern team in Valparaíso of Natalie Valentin, Beatriz Bolaños, and Max Eyes for their hard work in making the event a success and to Martha Rigby and Francisco Torres for their excellent job in directing and editing the Meet Claudio video.

Tomorrow's the big day~ come out to support the VSP at it's Boston Silent Auction at Impact Hub Boston, located at 50 Milk St. Boston, MA.

Tickets are $30 online (and can be found here: https://vspboston14.eventbrite.com/), or $40 at the door.

Join us for an evening of delicious food & drinks, as well as your chance to bid on great auction items from local artists and businesses. See you there!

column7:
Do you like clean beaches? So do we! Check out the latest blog post on VSP's beach clean as part of the Unidos Por Aguas Limpias campaign to read about our involvement & watch an awesome video capturing the day's success.
~~~~~~~
¿Te gusta playas limpias? ¡ Nosotros también! Revisa el último post del blog a ver la limpieza de la playa del VSP  como parte de la campaña Unidos Por Aguas Limpias. Aprovecha de leer de nuestra participación y de mirar un video bacán mostrando el exito del día. 

Save The Waves

http://valposurfproject.com/unidos-por-aguas-limpias-new-video/

column7:
It's been a week since wildfires raged through the city of Valparaíso and VSP has been doing all that it can to help in the recovery efforts.  Check out our latest blog post to see how the VSP and its supporters have been lending a hand!
http://bit.ly/1pjhPJD
~~~~~
Ha sido una semana desde que los incendios causara estragos en la ciudad de Valparaíso y VSP ha estado haciendo todo lo que puede para ayudar en los esfuerzos de recuperación. ¡Revise nuestro último post del blog para ver cómo el VSP y sus partidarios han estado dando una mano!

column7: #FUERZAVALPO Today the VSP and #volunteers head up the hills to take part in the clearing & reconstruction of the destroyed areas after the catastrophic wildfires that spread thru Valparaiso this weekend. #pontevalpo #valposurf

column7:
Saludos Todos!

Si alguien le interesa, quiero avisarles que mañana estamos juntando voluntarios a la Casa VSP a las 9:30am para ir a ayudar a una familia que conocemos. 

Si les gustaría venir, por favor traigan con Uds: agua y comida para sus mismos para almorzar, bloqueador, zapatos firmes/duros, mascarillas, algo para proteger a los ojos y guantes. Si pueden, también traigan palas, rastrillos, y bolsas de basura/cajas de cartón. 

NO TRAIGAN objetos personales de valor (cámaras, dinero, iphones, etc) porque desafortunadamente todavía hay algunas personas aprovechando.

También pueden compartir esta información si tienen amigos interesados. Muchísimas gracias y un abrazo enorme a todos. Cualquier consulta o duda, nos avisen por Face o el celular del equipo: 56515052. ¡Fuerza Valpo!

I have family in Cerro Playa Ancha and I'd love to help.', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31062433'}, {u'message': u'Take care of each other... Thinking of you all!!', u'from': {u'name': u'Ella Farnsworth', u'id': u'779704987941'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31063371'}, {u'message': u'Just heard about the fire. Glad to hear you guys are ok. If we want to send supplies where do we send them?', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31067829'}, {u'message': u'Se  puede hacer llegar a traves de cruz roja?', u'from': {u'name': u'Ofelia Moreno', u'id': u'696029983827524'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31069439'}, {u'message': u'Jim, I'm heading back to Chile on Wednesday---I've been in the US for my sister's wedding.  If you guys have school supplies and/or toiletries that you'd like to donate, I'm going to fill an extra bag with materials to bring down.  My number is 908-216-7056, I can swing by to pick stuff up.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075125'}, {u'message': u'I will definitely put some stuff together for you guys. And I'm working in Princeton so you can swing by there if you want', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075193'}, {u'message': u'Anything specific in terms of toiletries that you need Jon Steuber', u'from': {u'name': u'Jim Hayes', u'id': u'10203625485531955'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075212'}, {u'message': u'Hey Jim, based on what the collection points around Valpo are asking for, the most needed toiletries are things like: toothbrushes and toothpaste, feminine products (pads, tampons), soap, and wet wipes/moist towelette type things. Also, everyone has stopped collecting clothes except for NEW underwear.', u'from': {u'name': u'Martha Rigby', u'id': u'10203103687336182'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075283'}, {u'message': u'Also, Jim, I think that diapers might be a good space/weight ratio for something to bring down since I'll have about 50 pounds allotted in my other checked bag.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075309'}, {u'message': u'Hey Moises, I'll send you a private message.  Make sure to check your "Other Messages" folder where it will probably end up since we aren't facebook friends.', u'from': {u'name': u'Jon Steuber', u'id': u'786163120787'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075334'}, {u'message': u'Jon thanks for the response. I'm in Los Angeles, Ca aside from a wire transfer I'd be more than happy to gather some toiletries and other supplies for you and Mail it via DHL. I know there's a DHL office there in Valpo. My family in Valpo is ok. I was just there last month and anything I can do for you guys if be more than happy.', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075453'}, {u'message': u'Jon I'd also like to send some face masks for volunteers assisting in the impact zones along with Kevlar lined gloves. Based on photos I've seen the masks are not doing much to filter the dirt and smoke they are coming in contact with. The gloves also don't appear that good. Get me a list please. I've friend requested you and just waiting on your message. Thanks', u'from': {u'name': u'Moises Alvarez', u'id': u'614918775280227'}, u'id': u'10152323622092403_31075503'}], u'summary': {u'total_count': 14, u'order': u'chronological'}}

column7:
Hola a todos y todas. Por favor NO traigan ni ropa ni comida. Lo que mas necesitamos es lo siguiente:
-materiales de construcción (palas, carretillas, claves, guantes, etc.)
-artículos de aseo
-agua
-útiles escolares
Gracias a tod@s. Pronto vamos a organizar un plan para movilizar e ayudar a reconstruir lo que ha sido quemado. Les esperamos acá en Garibaldi 105 en Cerro La Cruz. ¡Fuerza Valpo!
_________________________________________________

Hello everyone. Please DO NOT bring food or clothes. What we need the most is the following:
-building materials (shovels, wheelbarrows, nails, gloves, etc.)
-toiletries
-water
-school supplies
Thank you everyone. Soon we are going to make a plan to mobilize and help to rebuild that which has been burned. We are here at the Casa VSP at Garibaldi 105 in Cerro La Cruz. Strength to Valpo!

column7:
Hola a todos y todas, esperamos que están a salvo. Estamos acá en la Casa VSP listos a aceptar donaciones de cualquier cosa para ayudar las víctimas del incendio de anoche. Por favor traigan comida, agua, ropa, pañales, guantes para sacar escombros, etc.
La Casa VSP ubica en Garibaldi 105, Cerro La Cruz. De la intersección Colon con Francia, sigue arriba por Francia y gira a la izquierda en Vallejos. La primera calle que se encuentra será Garibaldi, gira a la izquierda y estamos en la casa 105.
Quédense atentos hoy y en los próximos días. Estamos averiguando como podemos ayudar en la mejor manera posible; pronto vamos a organizar un grupo de voluntarios. 
___________________________________________________
Hello everyone, we hope you are all safe. We are here in the Casa VSP, ready to accept donations for victims of the fire last night. Please bring food, water, clothes, diapers, work gloves to remove rubble, etc.
The Casa VSP is located on 105 Garibaldi in Cerro La Cruz. From the intersection of Colon and Francia, continue towards the hills on Francia and turn left on Vallejos. The first street you see will be Garibaldi. Turn left there and we are in house number 105.
Stay tuned today and the next few days. We are figuring out how we can help in the best way possible; soon we will organize a group of volunteers.

column7:
El Mercurio featured the VSP in an article after our successful beach clean last Saturday. Give it a read to see how our project really impacts our local community and environment. This event was a part of the Unidos Por Aguas Limpias campaign, a national event to restore the Chilean coastline.
~~~~~~~~~
El Mercurio presento el VSP en un artículo después de nuestra exitosa limpieza de la playa el sábado pasado. Leélo para ver cómo nuestro proyecto impacta nuestra comunidad local y el medio ambiente. Este evento fue parte de la campaña Unidos Por Aguas Limpias, un evento nacional para restaurar la costa chilena.

column7:
Hey everyone! We did an outstanding job during our Saturday beach clean at Playa Portales...With 70 volunteers, we cleaned 75 big bags worth of garbage: 1,305 pounds of trash, of which 357 pounds were recyclable plastic & glass. Thanks to everyone who came and showed support!   
~~~~~~~
Saludos a todos, hemos hecho un trabajo maravilloso durante la limpieza de Playa Portales el sábado....Con 70 voluntarios, hemos limpiado: 75 bolsas grandes: 592 kilos de basura total: 162 kilos de plastico y vidrio reciclable. Muchísimas gracias a todos los que vinieron y apoyaron! 

#UxAL #UnidosPorAguasLimpias Save The Waves

column7:
Hey everyone, in just over a week the VSP will have it's first beach clean of the year at Playa Portales.  This event is part of Unidos Por Aguas Limpias, where costal beach cleans will happen across the country to encourage a clean environment & conscientious community!

When: Saturday, March 22 10:00-14:00
Where: Playa Diego Portales, southern side of Caleta Portales
 
~~~~~~~

Saludos a todos! En poco más de una semana, el VSP colaborá en la primera limpieza de playa del año en Playa Portales. El evento es parte de Unidos Por Aguas Limpias, en que limpiezas costales pasarán sobre todo el país a fomentar un ambiente limpio y una comunidad consciente. ¡Fuerza Chile!

Cuando: Sabado, el 22 de marzo, 10:00-14:00
Donde: Playa Portales, lado sureño de Caleta Portales

Save The Waves 
#UnidosPorAguasLimpias #UxAL

column7:
Here VSP is featured on Discovery Sports, Latin America's Discovery Channel page. A shout out to our friend, the author, Juan Manuel Daza who wrote the article after a visit Casa VSP. He even took to the sea with us and worked alongside our students! Give it a read it!
~~~~~~~~~~~
Aqui, el VSP, esta presentado por Discovery Deportes, la pagina de Discovery Latinoamericana. Un gran saludos a nuestro amigo, el autor, Juan Manuel Daza, quien escribió el artículo despues de un viaje a Casa VSP. También, él fue al mar con nosotros a colaborar con los estudiantes! Echalo!

http://deportes.tudiscovery.com/valpo-suf-projet-ayuda-a-nios-en-a-desarrollarse-junto-al-deporte/

Say hello to our newest group of students from Cerro Torro. Yesterday was their first time surfing and they had a blast! Couldn't have gotten to the beach without our JAC Chile Derco van!
~~~~~~~~~~
Saluda a nuestro grupo nuevo de estudiantes de Cerro Torro. Ayer fue su primer tiempo surfeando y divertían mucho! No pudo haber ido a la playa sin nuestra van de JAC Chile Derco!

On March 22, join the VSP and the United for Clean Waters campaign for a Chile-wide beach clean! Check out the VSP blog for the history of the event, VSP's involvement, photos from last year, and an awesome video. http://valposurfproject.com/united-for-clean-water/

Stay posted on the event details and how you can get involved here, and on the event page: https://www.facebook.com/events/209583935906451/

column7:
Even though it's been a few foggy days in Valpo, we're up in Cerro Torro, picking up our newest group of students to head to the beach in our JAC Chile Derco van! 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Aunque el clima ha sido poco nublado aquí en Valpo, estamos en Cerro Torro, recogiendo los estudiantes del grupo nuevo para ir a la playa in el van JAC Chile Derco!

column7:
And another week in the books! Here the Valpo Surf Project is packing up our JAC Chile Derco van headed back to Valparaíso after lots of waves and rays! We couldn't be happier to do what we're doing!
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
¡Y otra semana en los libros! Aquí Valpo Surf Project está arrenglando nuestro JAC Chile Derco van a volver a Valparaíso después de muchas olas y rayos. No podríamos estar más felices de hacer lo que estamos haciendo.

http://valposurfproject.com/spotlight-brainstorm-print-and-design/

column7:
Hey everyone! What a week we've had teaching surf lessons at La Boca! Due to a northwest swell, the waves have been wild and here, our students from Cerro Toro are ready for more! And where would we be without our JAC Chile and Derco VSP van?! 
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
Saludos a todos! Que semana increíble que hemos tenido enseñando lecciones de surf en La Boca! Por la marejada noroeste, las olas han sido locas! Y aquí nuestros estudiantes de Cerro Toro están listos para más! Donde estaríamos sin el caravan de JAC Chile y Derco! Gracias!

column7: We are very proud of our student, Nikolas Corvalan, who is leaving tomorrow to begin his career in the Chilean Navy. Nik has been a role model for our younger students in and out of the classroom. We will miss Nikolas, but we are excited to see what the future holds for this young man. Although he is leaving Valparaiso he will always be a part of the @valposurfproject family.     / / /    Estamos muy orgullos de nuestro alumno, Nikolas Corvalan, quién se va a empezar su carrera con la armada mañana. Nik ha sido un ejemplo para seguir. Le vamos a echar de menos y le deseamos lo mejor en todo. Aunque se va de Valparaíso siempre va a ser parte de la familia VSP.

column7:
Here's a photo from the first week of surf sessions at Playa La Boca in ConCon! Say hello to our new students from Cerro Toro. Wicked thankful to have our new JAC Chile and Derco sponsored van—to the beach & back! 

Hay una foto de la primera semana de surf aqui en Playa La Boca en ConCon! Saluda nuestra estudiantes nuevos de Cerro Toro! Súper agradecido a tener el nuevo van de JAC Chile y Derco—a la playa!

column7:
A big welcome to the newly arrived interns who will be joining the VSP staff for 2014.  After orientation, full programming begins next week with the new VSP van from JAC Chile and Derco!

Un bienvenido gigante a los practicantes que llegaron recién, quienes se sumarán al equipo de VSP en 2014.  Después de orientación, programación empieza la semana que viene con la nueva van de Jac Chile y Derco!

column7:
We made it!  Thanks to all of the generous support from our donors, we reached our stretch goal of $15,000 to fund expansion in 2014.  Thank you to everyone who contributed this holiday season! 

Lo logramos! Gracias a todo el apoyo de nuestros donadores, alcanzamos la meta de $15,000 para apoyar nuestra expansión en 2014.  Gracias a todos que contribuyeron durante el fin del año!

We're almost there!  The support this holiday season has been incredible!  We're currently $1,600 away from meeting our $15,000 goal for expansion in 2014.  

Every donation has an important impact on our students.  Please check out our annual appeal letter at http://us2.campaign-archive2.com/?u=1fb786b7dff8dae3d5c570968&id=a8c624a902 to see how your donation will impact the program and consider donating before the new year!

column7:
We are looking for smart, creative, self-starting young people to serve as interns and help take the VSP to another level. 

Interns will gain valuable experience, have a voice and an impact in a small but growing non-profit, have an amazing time in an amazing country, and most of all, help out a group of kids who really need it. Applications for a July 2014 start date are due by December 31.

More info at: http://valposurfproject.com/1160-2/ 

Please share and help get the word out!

After much time and effort, we're proud to premiere our 2013 video appeal. This year, more than ever, your donation is crucial to the continued success of the Valpo Surf Project. Please like, share, and make a donation to contribute to changing the lives of youth in Valparaíso and beyond: https://vimeo.com/79535186 (Subtitled in English)

Después de mucho tiempo y trabajo, estamos muy orgullosos para estrenar nuestro video del 2013. Este año, Ahora, mas que nunca, su donación es integral al éxito continuo del Valpo Surf Project. Por favor, ponga me gusta, difundir, y hacer una donación para contribuir a cambiar las vidas de jóvenes en Valparaíso y mas allá: https://vimeo.com/79535185 (Subtitled in Spanish)

Hoy día a las 15:30, VSP presentará en la Universidad de Playa Ancha, a través de la Dirección General Vinculación con el Medio, del programa que realizar en Valparaíso.  La presentación estará en Sala Carlos Pantoja, 2° piso de Casa Central.

Today VSP will be presenting at the Universidad de Playa Ancha, through the Dirección General Vinculación con el Media, about its programming in Valparaíso.  The presentation will be in Sala Carlos Pantoja, 2nd floor of Casa Central.

column7:
The VSP is again accepting applications for its year-long internship program for internships beginning in JULY 2014!  We’re looking for motivated and enthusiastic young people to help this growing organization and to get involved with many different aspects of our operations, including teaching and program logistics, development and strategy, and marketing communications.  

Please check out http://valposurfproject.com/1160-2/ for more information and to download an application!

Applications are due on December 31, 2013!

column7:
Vengan a asistir al FICSURF CHILE - Festival Internacional de Cine de Surf, el 28-30 de Noviembre en la Corporación Cultural Las Condes, en Santiago.  The Valpo Surf Project ha sido elegido como una organización beneficiaria del evento y después de comprar su entrada, pueden donar 100% del valor de la entrada a nuestro programa!  Apoyan a cultura del surf en Chile!

Come check out the FICSURF CHILE - International Surf Film Festival, from November 28-30 at the Corporación Cultural Las Condes in Santiago.  Valpo Surf Project has been chosen as a participating organization of the event and after purchasing tickets, you can donate 100% of the ticket value to our program! Come support Chilean surf culture!

http://bit.ly/1bdO9AP Check out some photos on the VSP blog of the Los Angeles Fundraising Event this past summer. A huge thanks to Katie Burns, our event organizer, and all the members of the organizing committee, including Jennifer Pollick, Jan Burns, and Joey Brighton Reynolds, and the Burns and Gilbert families for all of their support over the years. 

Les dejamos con algunas fotos en el blog de VSP del evento de recaudar fondos de Los Angeles este verano. Muchas gracias a Katie Burns, la organizadora del evento, y todos los miembros del comité de organización, incluyendo Jennifer Pollick, Jan Burns, y Joey Brighton Reynolds, y las familias Burns y Gilberto por todo su apoyo durante los años.

column7:
On Saturday, October 19, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its 5th Annual NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser at the Centre for Social Innovation in Manhattan. The event was our most successful fundraiser to date, with more than 125 people in attendance and generous support from our presenting sponsors Ketel One, Kona Brewing Company, and Runa Clean Energy, helping to raise funds to carry out our mission using surfing as a tool to engage inner city youth in Valparaíso, Chile.

The event attendants enjoyed an evening of food, drinks, and casting bids on an array of great gear and prizes available for silent auction. We’d like to thank the silent auction contributors for their generous support for making this event such a success. A huge thanks to surfboard shapers Monroe Surf Co. and  Malwitz Custom Surfboards, surf photographers Chris Burkard Photography, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Matt Clark and Nolan Hall; fine artists Brainstorm Print + Design, Billy Name, the archival photographer of Andy Warhol’s Factory,Scott Szegeski, Virginia Lunt, and illustrator Matt Caputo; Chronicle Books; Archive New York, Guns Germs $teal, Rosa Swim, Toms Shoes; Williams Sonoma, Riverhorse Brewing Company, Industry City Distillery, and the Manhattan Sailing School.

Attendees got to see a sneak peek of a mini-documentary video of the Valpo Surf Project, produced by Billy Manchuck and Pancho Torres, and the premiere of the VSP’s Ambassdors Program, featuring professional surfers Kurt Rist and Christian “Punto” Gonzalez.

The Valpo Surf Project would especially like to thank all of the volunteers who helped to make this our most successful event to date; without your support this event wouldn’t have been possible. Thanks to our volunteer committee, including Lindsay Steuber, Pat Flaherty, Margaret Ryan, and Jenna Barzelay, who contributed time and energy to plan and execute this event. We’d also like to thank everyone who worked as volunteers to make this event a huge success including Jeff and Ann Marie Steuber, Michael Knapp, Briana Feola and Jason Snyder of Brainstorm, Caitlyn Warakomski, Britney Warakomski, Sam Rigby, Kathryn Armstrong, Ryan Holbrook, and Matt Caputo for t-shirt printing.  

And a huge thank you to Andrew Karp at the Centre for Social Innovation NYC for hosting the event at their incredible space, and Ketel One, Kona Brewing Company, and Runa for their incredible support.

column7:
The whole VSP team would like to thank everyone involved in making last Saturday's NYC Silent Auction Fundraiser the most successful event to date.  Our most heartfelt thanks goes out to the volunteers, donors, sponsors and attendees; without you, none of this would be possible.  We'll have more photos up later this week and look forward to the online premiere of the video screened in mid November!

Todo el equipo VSP quiere agradecer todos involucrados para hacer el evento en NYC del sábado pasado, nuestro evento mas exitoso hasta ahora.  Nuestras gracias sinceras va a todos los voluntarios, donadores, auspiciadores, y asistentes; sin ustedes, esto no habría sido posible.  Publicamos mas fotos en la semana y todos deben estar atentos al estreno online del video que mostramos durante el evento en noviembre!

http://www.valposurfproject.com/internship-program/ 

Come intern with the VSP beginning in 2014 and join our team to help with operations and expansion in Valparaíso.  

Don't surf?  Not a problem--we're looking for young, motivated, self-starting leaders to contribute to the VSP. 

Act fast--applications are due this upcoming September 30!

column7:
As the winter months fade into spring, VSP surf sessions are starting back up on a consistent basis and our students are fully motivated.  The water's warming up, the sun's starting to shine and participants are donning neoprene to get back into the surf. Check out some more photos at http://bit.ly/17dNkJd for the latest sessions.

______________

Mientras que los meses del invierno cambian a primavera, las sesiones de surf de VSP están empezando con consistencia y nuestros estudiantes están motivados.  El agua empieza a entibiar, el sol está saliendo y los participantes están listos en sus trajes para meterse al surf.  Revisan algunas de las fotos de las últimas sesiones http://bit.ly/17dNkJd.

column7:
CPR Classes with Naval Rescue Swimmer | Clases de RCP con Nadador de Rescate

Last year, Chilean Naval rescue swimmer Joel Acevedo gave a comprehensive CPR tutorial to a group of older VSP participants in conjunction with English classes.  Acevedo incorporated his experience with open ocean swimming and rescue operations to deliver an informative lesson about assessing situational risk and the proper CPR technique.

A big thanks to Joel Acevedo for leading this class and teaching VSP students valuable skills that will help improve their confidence in the surf and dealing with emergency situations. 

El año pasado, nadador de rescate de la armada chilena, Joel Acevedo, dio una clase comprensiva de RCP a un grupo de nuestros alumnos mayores durante una sesión de inglés. Él incorporó su experiencia con natación en mar abierto y métodos de rescate para entregar a nuestros estudiantes una lección bien informativa sobre evaluación de riesgos y técnica correcta de RCP

Miles de gracías para Joel por enseñar a los participantes del VSP habilidades valiosas que les ayudarán a subir su confianza en las olas y las situaciones de emergencia.

Huge swell hitting Central Chile today!  Rest assured we're not doing surf classes w/ our participants in these conditions, but good luck and take care to those who have a surf today.    

¡Marejada gigante hoy día en la costa central de Chile!  Tengan la seguridad que nosotros no vamos a hacer clases de surf en estas condiciones con nuestros participantes, pero a todos que van a surfear hoy: buena suerte y cuídense.

column7:
Mientras que el semestre termina, el VSP le gustaría agradecer a nuestro equipo de voluntarios, la mayoría de los cuales están estudiando como estudiantes de intercambio en Valparaíso, por el tiempo y la pasión que han dedicado a la organización en los últimos meses. El éxito de la organización sólo es posible con su ayuda y apoyo incansable. Gracias a todos! Los vamos a echar de menos!

As the university semester ends in Chile, the VSP would like to thank our volunteer team, most of whom are studying as exchange students in Valparaíso, for the time and passion that they've dedicated to the organization over the last months. The success of the organization is only possible with your tireless help and support. Thank you all! We're going to miss you!

column7: Al principio de mayo, Valpo Surf Project se vinculó con varias organizaciones medioambientales sin fines de lucro para trabajar con mas de 115 voluntarios en una limpieza de playa en Caleta Portales, una de las playas principales de Valparaíso.    Por estar asociado con el Greenpeace - Equipo de Voluntarios Valparaíso, Sea Shepherd Chile, Valpo Interviene, and Rotaract Club of Valparaíso, un equipo de participantes y voluntarios recogieron 400 kilos de basura y materiales reciclables de la playa.  Aseguran a revisar el link al video de la limpieza abajo y las fotos del evento.  In early May, the Valpo Surf Project teamed up with a number of local environmental non-profits and engaged more than 115 volunteers in a beach clean at Playa Caleta Portales, one of Valparaíso’s principal beaches.       By partnering up with the Valparaíso Chapter of Greenpeace, Sea Shepherd Chile, Valpo Interviene, and Rotaract Club of Valparaíso, a team of VSP participants and volunteers collected more than 400 kilograms of trash and recyclable materials from the beach.  Make sure to check out the link to the video below and the photos of the event.   http://vimeo.com/66357759

column7:
El 5 de Junio, cinco voluntarios de VSP viajaron hacia el sur a Pichilemu para ver el Quiksilver Ceremonial de 2013 presentado por Subaru. Desafortunadamente, el campeonato fue cancelado porque las olas nunca alcanzaron los 7 metros predecidos. A pesar de todo, los espectadores disfrutaron 2 horas de una “Sesión de Expresión” de 24 de los mejores surfistas del mundo.

----------------------------------

On June 5th, five VSP volunteers packed up and headed south to catch The 2013 Quiksilver Ceremonial Chile presented by Subaru. The wave competition was unfortunately canceled due to an originally projected 15 foot-swell not reaching the necessary heights. Despite the cancelation, spectators were treated to a two hour “Expression Session” by 24 of the worlds best surfers.

column7:
Gran video de Mauricio Donoso M de Schiestl Chile Surf Boards  y su obra de fabricar tablas en Pichilemu.  Nos ayudó construir una tabla con nuestros estudiantes el año pasado. Gracias por todo el apoyo sobre los años! 

Great video of VSP supporter Mauricio Donoso M, owner of Schiestl Chile Surf Boards, and his shaping operation in Pichilemu.  He helped us hand shape a board with our students last year. Thanks for all the support over the years!

column7:
Falta poco hasta la gran limpieza de Playa Portales! Mañana a las 10--ven a echar una mano por la campaña nacional FUERZA CHILE! UNIDOS POR AGUAS LIMPIAS con Save The Waves and Vigilante Costero Maule Itata! 

Not much time left until the big beach clean at Playa Portales! Tomorrow at 10--come lend a hand in the national campaign FUERZA CHILE! UNIDOS POR AGUAS LIMPIAS with Saves the Waves and Vigilante Costero Maule Itata!

column7:
Ven a ayudarnos limpiar Playa Portales este sábado 23 de Marzo, a las 10:00-14:00!  Mas información en el evento: http://www.facebook.com/events/213088888836838/

Come help us clean Playa Portales this Saturday March 23 at 10:00-14:00! More information in the event page: http://www.facebook.com/events/213088888836838/

_______________________

Punto de Encuentro: Playa Portales al lado sureño de Caleta Diego Portales 
Direcciones: Ubicado en Avenida España entre Valparaíso y Viña del Mar, también se puede usar el metro y bajar en estación Portales.

column7:
Learn about the VSP’s new skate program and how you can help by donating skateboards, skateboard accessories, and safety gear, PARTICULARLY HELMETS!  If you are located in the New York City, Miami, or Los Angeles area---or are willing to ship to those areas--- please contact jsteuber@valposurfproject.com if you have gear you would like to donate!    

Aprende mas del programa de skate de VSP y como puedes ayudar por donar patinetas y accessorios de patinaje, incluyendo equipo de seguridad, PARTICULARMENTE CASCOS!  Si estás en Santiago o Valparaíso/Viña del Mar y tienes algo para donar por favor contacta con jsteuber@valposurfproject.com.    
________________________________    

Throughout the summer months the Valpo Surf Project opened up a new series of skateboarding and rollerblading classes available to our students.  Skate classes have been a great way to motivate students to stay active and fit for surfing when we didn’t have the resources to get to the beach.    

While the skate club has had humble beginnings with a few pair of donated rollerblades and borrowed skateboards, we want to expand the resources to offer skate classes to more students.  Our first priority in moving forward with skateboard classes is to ensure the safety of our students.  We are very much in need of safety equipment so please contact jsteuber@valposurfproject.com to coordinate an in kind donation.    _________________________________   

Durante los meses del verano, Valpo Surf Project empezó un nuevo taller de patinaje (con patines y patinetas) disponibles para nuestros estudiantes.  Las clases de patinaje han sido una buena manera para motivar los estudiantes a ser activos y en forma para el surf cuando no hemos tenido los recursos a llegar a la playa.  

Mientras que el taller de patinaje ha tenido origen humilde con algunos patines donados y patinetas prestadas, queremos expandir los recursos para ofrecer clases de patinaje para mas estudiantes.  Nuestra prioridad principal en seguir adelante con los talleres es asegurar la seguridad de los estudiantes.  Nosotros necesitamos equipo de seguridad así que por favor contacta con jsteuber@valposurfproject.com para coordinar su donación.

column7:
Al final de enero el equipo Valpo Surf Project fue a las playas Baron y Placeres para limpiar dos de las playas principales de la ciudad que estaban llenas de basura tirada durante las celebraciones del Año Nuevo en Valparaíso.  Organizado por el Sea Shepherd Conservation Society Chile, el Valpo Surf Project juntó mas que 25 voluntarios y estudiantes para juntarse con mas que 100 voluntarios de otras organizaciones en esta gran limpieza.  Otras organizaciones participantes incluyen los cuerpos de voluntarios de Sea Shepherd de la V Región y Región Metropolitana, Servicio Nacional de Menores (SENAME), Cuerpo de Botes Salvavidas de Valparaíso, la Municipalidad de Valparaíso y el Puerto Deportivo de Valparaíso.  

Gracias a todos los voluntarios y estudiantes que vinieron para apoyar esta actividad para proteger los océanos de la región costera de Valparaíso.        ____________________________________  

At the end of January the Valpo Surf Project team headed to Valparaíso’s Playa Baron and Playa Placeres to clean two of the city’s principal beaches that had been scattered with trash after Valparaíso’s New Year’s celebrations.  Organized by Sea Shepherd Conservation Society Chile, the Valpo Surf Project brought together 25 volunteers and students to join more than 100 volunteers from other organizations in this large scale beach clean.  Other participating organizations included members of Sea Shepherd from Chile’s 5th Region and Metropolitan Region, Servicio Nacional de Menores (SENAME), Cuerpo de Botes Salvavidas de Valparaíso, the Municipality of Valparaíso, and the Puerto Deportivo of Valparaíso.    

Thanks to all of the volunteers and students who came out to support this latest effort to protect the water quality of Valparaíso’s coastal region.

New Year's is always a great time in Valparaiso. Hopefully next year the adults can step up and be responsible the mess left in the wake of the party. Fortunately, the VSP kids were there to do some major clean up at the city's beaches after the festivities concluded.

El Año Nuevo siempre es una noche increible en Valparaiso. Ojala que el proximo año los adultos puedan ser responsable por su basura despues de la fiesta. Gracias a los alumnos del VSP que tomaron la responsibilidad de limpiar algunas de las playas de Valparaiso.

column7:
Today is the last day to make tax deductible donations for 2012! We are just $1,800 shy of reaching our fundraising goal of $10,000 this holiday season. The VSP was created by small donations from all of you, and we need your support for continued success. Please take a moment and give whatever you can to help us reach our goal. Every gift has a major impact on our students' lives.

Thank you so much and we wish you all a very happy new year!

http://www.valposurfproject.com/donate-now/

column7:
Jueves el 20 de Diciembre el VSP  llevó a cabo el primer evento para recaudar fondos  en Chile en Zen Club Boutique, el innovador restaurante de sushi y discoteque en Santiago.  Todos los fondos recaudados del evento van a beneficiar la Vanpaign, nuestra campaña de recaudar fondos para una nueva van para la organización.  Fue un gran éxito con mucha gente y una noche de diversión incluyendo tragos, sushi y rifas de Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer’s Paradise, y Deportes Tenderini. 

Gracias a todos los que vinieron a apoyar el VSP, todos los voluntarios que ayudaron a hacer el evento exitoso, A Lo Gringo por proveer la música, y todos los auspiciadores del evento incluyendo Zen Club Boutique, Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer’s Paradise, y Deportes Tenderini.  Y muchas gracias a Fernanda Vallade por organizar el evento!   
 ______________________________    

On Thursday December 20th, the VSP hosted its first fundraising event in Chile at Zen Club Boutique, Santiago’s premiere night club and sushi bar.  All proceeds raised from the event will benefit the Vanpaign, our campaign to purchase a new van for the organization.  The event was a great success with a packed house, and fun night with drinks, sushi and raffle prizes from Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer’s Paradise, and Deportes Tenderini.    

Thanks to everyone who came out to support the VSP, everyone who volunteered and helped to make the event a success, A Lo Gringo for providing a great soundtrack, and all of the sponsors of the event including Zen Club Boutique, Voraz Pizza Vitacura, Juan Pablo Barrientos, Surfer’s Paradise, and Deportes Tenderini.  And a huge thank you to Fernanda Vallade for organizing the event!

column7:
Evento a Beneficio de Valpo Surf Project en ZEN entre las 19:00 y 23:00 hrs. este Jueves 20 de Diciembre. Donación sugerida de $5.000 que incluye un vino, un trago y participación del sorteo de un vale por $20.000 en Voraz Pizza Vitacura. 

Tambien habrán rifas con premios auspiciados por Surfers Paradise Chile - Surf shop, Deportes Tenderini, Juan Pablo Barrientos de la Escuela de Surf Chile Extremo (Con Con) y clases Surf por Valpo Surf Project.

Banda invitada: 
- A LO GRINGO 

Después celebraremos toda la noche junto a:
- DJ Leonardo Vargas
- DJ BYTE

Fundraiser for VSP at ZEN, this Thursday December 20 in Providencia, Santiago. 5.000 suggested donation that includes a glass of wine, a cocktail, and door prize raffle for a $20.000 gift certificate to Voraz Pizza. 

There will also be raffles from Surfers Paradise Chile, Deportes Tenderini, Juan Pablo Barrientos of Escuela de Surf Chile Extremo in Concón, and private surf classes from the Valpo Surf Project.

Guest Band: A LO GRINGO

Then we will celebrate all night with:
DJ Leonardo Vargas
DJ Byte

Todos las recaudaciones irán a la campaña de recaudar fondos para un medio de transporte (Vanpaign) / All funds from this event will benefit the Vanpaign our campaign for a mode of transportation.

column7:
After a successful first 10K race in September, the VSP running team took up the challenge again this past Sunday, October 21st, at the Third Annual Family Run held by the Firefighters Association of Viña del Mar.  

Congratulations to VSP participant Nik Corvalan (age 17) for finishing in the top 20 and congratulations to Catalina Pulgar Nuñez and Ayleen Flores for reducing their 10K time by 17 minutes in just 20 days – an incredibly impressive feat!   

Special thanks to cofounder Andres Ponce and volunteer Michelle Fernández for running with VSP participants and supporting VSP in this grueling race.  The VSP team looks forward to many more successful runs in the future!       

Después de una corrida exitosa de 10K en septiembre, el equipo VSP corrió nuevamente este domingo 21 de octubre, la 3da Corrida Familiar del Cuerpo de Bomberos de Viña del Mar.  

Felicitaciones a alumno de VSP Nik Corvalan (17) quien llegó a los veinte primeros y felicitaciones a alumnas Catalina Pulgar Nuñez (13) and Ayleen Flores (17) por bajando su tiempo de 10K por 17 minutos – un logro increíble!   

Muchas gracias a co-fundador Andrés Ponce y voluntaria Michelle Fernández por correr con el equipo VSP y apoyarnos en esta ardua tarea.  El equipo VSP espera tener muchas más corridas exitosas en el futuro!

Special thanks to our friends at Reader to Reader, an NGO based in Amherst, Massachusetts, for their amazing book donations! Last week we surprised the kids with some of the new books and they were thrilled. After browsing through all of them and picking their favorites, we sat down together and started reading. Thanks!

Muchas gracias a nuestros amigos de “Reader to Reader,” una ONG ubicada en Amherst, MA, EEUU, por sus donaciones de libros! La semana pasada sorprendimos a los chicos con los nuevos libros y estaban súper emocionados. Después de que revisaron los libros, eligieron sus favoritos, y nos sentamos con ellos a leer juntos. Gracias!

column7:
This past Sunday, September 30, the VSP family took a break from surfing to show off their athletic prowess at the 2nd Annual TPS Marathon.  Congratulations to VSP participants Catalina Pulgar Nuñez (age 13), Ayleen Flores (age 17), and Nik Corvalan (age 17) for their amazing effort in training for and finishing the grueling 10K race.  Thanks to their hard work, Catalina placed 96th in her age group, Ayleen placed 31st, and Nik placed 13th out of over 3,000 race participants.  Together with volunteers Brendan Buckland, Luna Toledo, and Michelle Fernández, these VSP stars ran through Valpo’s scenic port area while proudly sporting their VSP caps and face paint.

Special thanks to the fans who came to support the VSP team: VSP Cofounder and Director Henry Myer, VSP participant Bárbara del Canto, volunteers Camila Valenzuela and Claudio Vilches, and proud VSP parents Mrs. Yanina Corvalan and Mr. Flores.  Eager to run again, the VSP family will also be running in the 3rd Annual Firefighter Association of Viña del Mar 10K race on October 21st.  We hope to see you there!



Este domingo pasado, la familia VSP suspendió sus sesiones semanales de surf para mostrar su proeza atlética en la segunda media maratón de Valparaíso.  Felicitaciones a los alumnos de VSP que participaron - Catalina Pulgar Nuñez (13), Ayleen Flores (17), y Nik Corvalan (17) – por sus esfuerzos y dedicación increíble a entrenar y terminar esta carrera durísima de 10 kilómetros.  Gracias a sus esfuerzos, Catalina ganó el 96 lugar de su categoría de edad, Ayleen ganó el 31 lugar, y Nik ganó el 13 lugar entre más de 3 mil participantes en la corrida.  Junto con voluntarios Brendan Buckland, Luna Toledo, y Michelle Fernández, estas estrellas de VSP corrieron orgullosamente por el puerto pintoresco de Valpo con sus gorros y caras pintadas con las letras de VSP.

Muchas gracias a los fans que vinieron a apoyar al equipo de VSP: co-fundador y director de VSP Henry Myer, alumna de VSP Bárbara del Canto, voluntarios Camila Valenzuela y Claudio Vilches, y padres orgullosos de VSP Sra. Yanina Corvalan y Sr. Flores.  Emocionados por correr de nuevo, la familia VSP correrá en la Corrida Familiar de los Bomberos de Viña del Mar el 21 de Octubre.  Esperamos verlos allí!

column7:
This past Saturday September 15, the Valpo Surf Project hosted its 4th Annual Silent Auction Fundraiser in New York City, with more than 65 people in attendance.  Held on the rooftop terrace of the Associated Press offices, the event brought together long time supporters in the NYC area and engaged new donors who came to learn more about the VSP mission.    

The evening was a great opportunity to celebrate and sustain the work of the Valpo Surf Project and the event’s success was possible only through the active support of so many people.  We would like to thank everyone who came out to attend the event, Pat Flaherty and everyone at the Associated Press for allowing us to use their space,  Kona Brewing Company and Ketel One Vodka for the beverages, Ann Marie Steuber for catering excellent food, Brainstorm Print and Design for crafting the event poster, and Lindsay Steuber for coordinating much of the silent auction donations, and all the volunteers who helped set up and break down the event.    

We’d also like to thank all of the contributors to our silent auction  Malwitz Custom Surfboards, Thomas Campbell, Chris Burkard, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Joe Hodnicki of Sharing the Stoke, Chronicle Books, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Eclectic Current Custom Kicks, Soul Polish Yoga, and Ann Marie Steuber.  
_________________  
Este Sábado pasado, el 15 de septiembre, Valpo Surf Project acogió su Cuarto Evento Anual de Recaudar fondos en New York City, con mas que 65 personas en asistencia.  Se llevó a cabo en la terraza de aire libre de las oficinas del Associated Press, el evento reunió a partidarios viejos y nuevos del Valpo Surf Project para ofrecer su apoyo y aprender más de las iniciativas nuevas del programa.  

La noche fue una grande oportunidad para celebrar y sostener el trabajo del Valpo Surf Project y el éxito del evento solo fue posible por el apoyo activo de mucha gente.  Nos gustaría dar gracias a la gente que asistió el evento, Pat Flaherty y todos del Associated Press por permitirnos a usar el espacio,  Kona Brewing Company y Ketel One Vodka por donar los tragos, Ann Marie Steuber por preparar la comida, Brainstorm Print and Design por diseñar el afiche del evento, Lindsay Steuber por coordinar muchas donaciones del remate, y toda la gente que nos ayudó a preparar antes de y limpiar despues del evento.  

También, nos gustaría dar las gracias también a toda la gente que contribuyeron al remate: Malwitz Custom Surfboards, Thomas Campbell, Chris Burkard, Ryan Struck, Kassia Meador, Joe Hodnicki of Sharing the Stoke, Chronicle Books, Brainstorm Print and Design, Matt Caputo, Eclectic Current Custom Kicks, Soul Polish Yoga, y Ann Marie Steuber.

column7:
Join us for the 4th Annual NYC Fundraiser and Silent Auction
When: Saturday, September 15, 7 PM-11 PM
Where: Rooftop Terrace of 450 W 33rd St. NY, NY  
Tickets: $40, available only for purchase online in advance (tickets available next week)

Tickets include appetizers and drinks by Ketel One and Kona Brewing Company

Featuring art and radness for silent auction from Kassia Meador Ryan Struck Photography Chris Burkard Photography Malwitz Custom Surfboards Sharing The Stoke Matt Cap Chronicle Books and many more.  

Stay tuned for more information on ticket sales.

column7:
Today we say good-bye to our dear friend Kathryn Armstrong, the founder/director of Foto Valpo. All of us here at the VSP are extremely proud of her and we will miss her love, leadership, and energy.

Kathryn began formulating the curriculum for Foto Valpo in 2010. After spending the summer and fall of 2011 fundraising with assistant Danielle Frye and VSP Development Director Wiley Todd she launched the Foto Valpo pilot program in March of 2012. Foto Valpo's first semester saw 16 VSP students participate and culminated in a wonderful exhibition of the students work on May 25, 2012.

Although Kathryn is returning home to Thomaston, Maine, USA she has left her mark on the Valpo Surf Project and Foto Valpo will continue on. We wish you the best Kathryn and hope you come back for a  visit soon!
